         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">21/9/86. ¶  ¶ In reply to your letter of the 11. Aug, dear Mr Ridley, ¶ Letter not found. ¶  ¶ let me say, that it seems best, not to disturbe the sets of Mr Forbes's plants for my benefit there. ¶ He...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">86.09.21</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Henry Ridley</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RBG Kew, Miscellaneous Correspondence, Mueller.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">21/9/86.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>In reply to your letter of the 11. Aug, dear Mr Ridley,<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Letter not found.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>let me say, that it seems best, not to disturbe the sets of Mr Forbes's plants for my benefit there.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Henry Forbes.</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>I will attend to the Dicotyledoneae so far as I have them here, except Euphorbiaceae, Urticeae and a few others (unless Ficus) as mentioned in my letter to your excellent Chief;<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See M to<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>W.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Carruthers,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>21 October 1885.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>to my observations then additions could later be made from the ampler material at your establishment. If you and your honored Colleagues will attend to the Mono- and Acotyledoneae meanwhile, we shall have in time a complete elaboration of Mr Forbes's plants. I am anxiously awaiting the results of his collecting in the vicinity of Dinner-island,<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn3" n="4">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Now Samarai, New Guinea.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>as these additions may complete in many instances the material of his first collecting, so many of the plants then being found only in flower or only in fruit. You will be aware yourself, that the determining of species with conscientious accuracy is a matter of time and patient research, and a<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">full</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>list of Mr Forbes's plants could therefore not be issued for a very considerable period. All that early could be done (particularly from the often incomplete material) would be, to name in many cases only the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">genera</hi>
               </seg>. In disposing of Mr Forbes's set of plants, it should be made a<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">condition</hi>
               </seg>, that the elaboration of the Dicotyledoneae - (with some exceptions) is<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">reserved</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">for</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Melbourne</hi>
               </seg>, so as to avoid clashing, and this arrangement is surely<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">fair</hi>
               </seg>, when it is considered, what heaps of undescribed plants from nearly all parts of the world are available for British Phytographers in your country. Of course, bona fide Monographers would always assert their claims. It should also be<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>borne in mind, that Mr Forbes —<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>without the Austral. geograph Society voting him £500 –<seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">"</seg>-<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">"</seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>on my proposition last year, —<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>could never have held his ground through the season in New Guinea.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I look forward with some interest to your opinion on my observations on the vaccineaceous Ericeae, and hope the notes sent by me will appear in Mr Britten's journal.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn4" n="5">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>B86.10.01.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I do not at all well understand the limits adopted for Agapetes and some other genera in recent works, and feel convinced, that they<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>should from augmenting material be recast, which you are sure to do in your excellent way for Ericeae soon.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I am now just working on the few as yet known Papuan Ternstroemiaceae. In reference to your question, when and where the publication of Mr F's plants should take place, let me say, that only<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">one course</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>is open to us, that of publishing any fragmentary elaboration whenever ready in some journals (an excellent one Mr Trimens)<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn5" n="6">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Error for<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>James<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Britten? Henry Trimen had been editor of the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Journal of b</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">otany</seg>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>until 1879, but did not edit<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>another journal when he went to Ceylon (<seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">TL2</seg>).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>and to collect these fragments finally for a complete elaboration.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">With regardful remembrance<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Acotyledoneae<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
            </p>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Agapetes</p>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Dicotyledoneae<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
            </p>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Ericeae<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
            </p>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Euphorbiaceae<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
            </p>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Ficus<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
            </p>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Monocotyledoneae<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
            </p>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Ternstroemiaceae<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
            </p>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Urticeae<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
            </p>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Vaccineaceae<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
            </p>
         </div>
      </body>
